latestPosts.caption:
If I ever made you feel insecure by giving the false impression of a flat tummy and a size zero figure, here is my apology to you ❤️ 

Every time I see someone posting a flat tummy, I squeeze my Caeserean paunch and sulk a little.. sometimes I struggle as much as every other person when a dress doesn’t have a flattering fit..

Posting this as a reminder to myself, to treat my body with kindness and love.. Now go give yourself a warm hug just like I did here ❤️ #bodypositivity #flexyourtummy #abs #selflovesunday

Here’s my story!

While I enter into my 36 with all the typical apprehensions and fear anyone would have, I also feel extremely grateful for all the moments I lucked out to have the life I have created for myself!

Took me a while now and I think I finally understand that it’s always about the journey and not the destination 💖 

#sassyredsenorita #happy36tome #singlemoms #divorcedmom #kitsungi #divorcednotbroken #birthdaypost

latestPosts.caption:
❣️Body dysmorphia 

2021 me flaunted this dress. 2023 me lost almost 7 kgs chasing an ab line, lifting mindlessly, constantly picking myself apart and this dress became too loose for me.. Then came the injuries… one after another. I couldn’t work out consistently for nearly two years. And yes, I have gained weight.

But it wasn’t just weight I gained — I gained a deeper understanding of my body and what it truly needs. 
I gained clarity on how real body dysmorphia can be, especially when you’ve lost weight after being a chubby kid your whole life. Even the smallest change on the scale can spiral into anxiety and obsession.

But today? This dress fits again — not because I shrank, but because I grew, not just in size but also in self compassion. Today, I’m one step ahead of who I was yesterday 💛

#BodyAcceptance #RealBodyJourney #HealingNotHustling #StrongNotSmall #ProgressNotPerfection #sassyredsenorita #bodydysmorphia
